Borussia Dortmund manager Jurgen Klopp has attacked Bayern Munich's conduct for admitting interest in Marco Reus and claims their comments could come back to bite them.

The Bundesliga champions have riled Klopp this week after Bayern Munich chairman Kerl-Heinz Rummenigge talked openly about a move for attacking midfielder Reus.

Klopp accused Bayern of kicking his side when they're down as Dortmund currently lie 15th in the Bundesliga ahead of their visit to league leaders Munich on Saturday.

