'In our current position, where this causes relatively little enjoyment, it is just not worth it,' added Klopp.

'However, I believe that life is fair. Whoever behaves badly while they succeed can get payback later.

'We currently do not have the problem of having to behave well during a period of success, because we are not in one,' he added.

Despite their poor form, Dortmund did beat Bayern 2-0 in the German Super Cup at the start of the season

 

